    "full_text": "- Hi, district leaders. I'm Victoria from Khan Academy. We're excited to share with\nyou some groundbreaking work that we're doing when it\ncomes to student assessments. We know districts are\nswamped with solutions that provide endless data, but fail to deliver\nreal, actionable insights that lead to greater student achievement. As we reimagine the\nKhan Academy experience for teaching and learning, we are now also introducing\ninterim assessments. Assessments that not\nonly measure progress, but give instructional leaders\nand teachers data, insights, and personalized student learning journeys to accelerate outcomes. I'll start by showing you\nwhat's already available, and then we'll look at what's\ncoming in the near future. This all builds on our use\nof responsible, effective AI. As part of a 45-minute assessment, students will see a range of item types, including a two-part explain\nyour thinking, or EYT item, facilitated by our new\nSocratic, conversational AI tool for assessments, Khanductor. After students respond to a\nmore traditional item type, Khanductor asks thoughtful\nfollow-up questions about the test concept to surface a student's deeper reasoning, uncovering conceptual understandings, and even unfinished learning that traditional right or\nwrong items can't reveal. Also, we're really inspired seeing that through the\nconversation With Khanductor, we're noticing that students are able to show more of what they know, even if they don't answer\nthe question correctly. A lot of research has gone\ninto developing Khanductor and its ability to gauge\na student's thinking. We're equally focused\non how those insights are reported in clear, usable ways to equip administrators and\nteachers with the tools needed to turn those insights\ninto stronger instruction and faster learning recovery. This is where reports come in, designed to deliver clear\ncomprehensive assessment reporting for all stakeholders. Teachers and administrators\nreceive more than just scores. They get deep, qualitative insights derived from these EYT chats. Assessment scores automatically generate personalized learning paths in the reimagined Khan Academy ecosystem, providing a clear roadmap\nto grade-level success for every student. Students build agency as they track their\nperformance and progress, celebrating success along the way with positive reinforcement\nand incentives. We are excited to offer you early access to this transformative teaching, learning, and assessment solution. Partner with us to give your\nstudents the opportunity to remediate unfinished learning and accelerate their journeys to grade-level success\nand on-time graduation. (bright music)"
